### Friendship flow — full coverage (send, accept, decline, cancel) with edge cases.
### Uses an isolated phone namespace (+33600000001..04) so it can run regardless
### of the other .http files. Reset friendships table between full runs if needed.

### Variables
@host = http://localhost:8080
@phoneA = +33600000001
@phoneB = +33600000002
@phoneC = +33600000003
@phoneD = +33600000004

### ─────────────────────────────────────────
### SETUP — register 4 users + login all of them
### ─────────────────────────────────────────

### 1. Register A (olfa)
POST {{host}}/users/register
Content-Type: application/json

{ "username": "olfa",  "password": "test123", "phoneNumber": "{{phoneA}}", "email": "olfa@test.com" }

### 2. Register B (alice)
POST {{host}}/users/register
Content-Type: application/json

{ "username": "alice", "password": "test123", "phoneNumber": "{{phoneB}}", "email": "alice@test.com" }

### 3. Register C (bob)
POST {{host}}/users/register
Content-Type: application/json

{ "username": "bob",   "password": "test123", "phoneNumber": "{{phoneC}}", "email": "bob@test.com" }

### 4. Register D (dan)
POST {{host}}/users/register
Content-Type: application/json

{ "username": "dan",   "password": "test123", "phoneNumber": "{{phoneD}}", "email": "dan@test.com" }

### 5. Login A → token
POST {{host}}/users/login
Content-Type: application/json

{ "phoneNumber": "{{phoneA}}", "password": "test123" }

> {% client.global.set("token", response.body); %}

### 6. Login B → tokenB
POST {{host}}/users/login
Content-Type: application/json

{ "phoneNumber": "{{phoneB}}", "password": "test123" }

> {% client.global.set("tokenB", response.body); %}

### 7. Login C → tokenC
POST {{host}}/users/login
Content-Type: application/json

{ "phoneNumber": "{{phoneC}}", "password": "test123" }

> {% client.global.set("tokenC", response.body); %}

### 8. Login D → tokenD
POST {{host}}/users/login
Content-Type: application/json

{ "phoneNumber": "{{phoneD}}", "password": "test123" }

> {% client.global.set("tokenD", response.body); %}

### ─────────────────────────────────────────
### SEND FRIEND REQUEST — happy path + error cases
### ─────────────────────────────────────────

### 9. A sends a friend request to B (expects 201, captures friendshipIdAB)
POST {{host}}/api/friendships
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{ "phoneNumber": "{{phoneB}}" }

> {% client.global.set("friendshipIdAB", response.body.id); %}

### 10. Same request again (expects 409 - already pending)
POST {{host}}/api/friendships
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{ "phoneNumber": "{{phoneB}}" }

### 11. Send to self (expects 409)
POST {{host}}/api/friendships
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{ "phoneNumber": "{{phoneA}}" }

### 12. Send to non-existing phone (expects 404)
POST {{host}}/api/friendships
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{ "phoneNumber": "+33699999999" }

### 13. Without token (expects 401)
POST {{host}}/api/friendships
Content-Type: application/json

{ "phoneNumber": "{{phoneB}}" }

### ─────────────────────────────────────────
### ACCEPT — uses friendshipIdAB; also exercises GET /received
### ─────────────────────────────────────────

### 14. B lists received requests (expects 200 with 1 PENDING)
GET {{host}}/api/friendships/received
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenB}}

### 15. B accepts (expects 200, status ACCEPTED)
POST {{host}}/api/friendships/{{friendshipIdAB}}/accept
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenB}}

### 16. Accept again (expects 409 - already processed)
POST {{host}}/api/friendships/{{friendshipIdAB}}/accept
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenB}}

### 17. A (the requester) tries to accept (expects 404 - not receiver)
POST {{host}}/api/friendships/{{friendshipIdAB}}/accept
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 18. Accept a non-existing friendship (expects 404)
POST {{host}}/api/friendships/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/accept
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenB}}

### ─────────────────────────────────────────
### DECLINE — separate flow with user C
### ─────────────────────────────────────────

### 19. A sends a friend request to C (expects 201, captures friendshipIdAC)
POST {{host}}/api/friendships
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{ "phoneNumber": "{{phoneC}}" }

> {% client.global.set("friendshipIdAC", response.body.id); %}

### 20. C declines (expects 200, status DECLINED)
POST {{host}}/api/friendships/{{friendshipIdAC}}/decline
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenC}}

### 21. Decline again (expects 409 - already processed)
POST {{host}}/api/friendships/{{friendshipIdAC}}/decline
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenC}}

### 22. A (the requester) tries to decline (expects 404 - not receiver)
POST {{host}}/api/friendships/{{friendshipIdAC}}/decline
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 23. Decline a non-existing friendship (expects 404)
POST {{host}}/api/friendships/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/decline
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenC}}

### ─────────────────────────────────────────
### CANCEL — separate flow with user D
### ─────────────────────────────────────────

### 24. A sends a friend request to D (expects 201, captures friendshipIdAD)
POST {{host}}/api/friendships
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

{ "phoneNumber": "{{phoneD}}" }

> {% client.global.set("friendshipIdAD", response.body.id); %}

### 25. A cancels (expects 200, status CANCELLED)
POST {{host}}/api/friendships/{{friendshipIdAD}}/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 26. Cancel again (expects 409 - already processed)
POST {{host}}/api/friendships/{{friendshipIdAD}}/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 27. D (the receiver) tries to cancel (expects 404 - not requester)
POST {{host}}/api/friendships/{{friendshipIdAD}}/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{tokenD}}

### 28. Cancel a non-existing friendship (expects 404)
POST {{host}}/api/friendships/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000/cancel
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}